caption: Backyard is really nice. Portions really small. No vegan options. No flexibility in sides, not even when asked for a slice of bread with the omelette. A lot of room for improvement.

Cute backyard patio but the menu was completely underwhelming. The mains are the size of appetizers and the appetizers are the size of a bite! Paying $8 for an arugula salad the size of your thumb should be illegal in 2021. The food itself was also underwhelming - the shakshuka had a very bland tomato sauce (no veggies) with 2 eggs (again in a very small dish).  For the price you pay, you’d expect better food.
Dishes with great potential were executed poorly. Portions were quite small for the price tag, and everything (especially the squid ink spaghetti) was too salty. Duck confit was alright.

This place has outdoor eating in the backyard of the place. The place is pricey but it is what it is during covid. They make up for it with wonderful service and great food. The food was great!!!! I ordered the eggplant risotto and the hot cider cocktail. Also, they use heat lamps. They have one bathroom. Also, the staff wears mask and maintain social distance. Again, The service was nice and the food was great.
Ridiculously rude hostess. No thanks
Aside from a surly hostess, a great place to eat. The food was good and the service was quick.

This place not only was really pretty and cozy for outdoor dining, the food was delicious, to the point I finished my plate. And the glass of wine I had paired completely with the dish. The menu is very small and extremely well thought. Last night we had the butternut squash lasagna and the pork ragu with focaccia. Also, the sous-chef went to almost all the tables to ask about the food. Beautiful place. Will come again.

If there's a place to dine out while it's still possible, this is it. The back garden honestly felt so tranquil it was unreal. Quiet and friendly. The servers were lovely and their recommendations all landed, even adapting to which dish to eat first in the cold. The dishes have this uncanny ability to feel both traditional and innovative simultaneously. Squash ravioli in kimchi brodo and a mixed mushroom pot pie were the highlights. But housemade ricotta and focaccia were also up to any standard.

Delicious food, very friendly, knowledgable and accommodating staff (great wine reccs) in a beautiful environment. The crab ravioli was so good, I ordered another round as soon as I’d finished it. The back garden is so romantic, laced with hanging lights with a large tree at the centre.
Good place for Italian food. Don't fret if it's busy, it is worth the wait. The service was very welcoming and sociable. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I liked.

Great dining spot, the backyard garden is the very cute and the perfect spot for a date night. Great wine selection, good Italian inspired cousin with a little American infusion. The gumbo is delicious.

Went here two weekends in a row it was so lovely.  Back patio is great, seating is Covid friendly, and our waitress (whom we had two weeks in a row, was great!  Absolutely recommend the focaccia, gazpacho,  the burrata, and the crispy chicken. All heavenly.  We tried the Campanelle, Tagliatelle, and mezze meinche and they were all only okay. The food I mentioned in the previous paragraph more than make up for it.  Based on how good the chicken was, cannot wait to try the rest of their mains.

Just OK, very pleasant backyard setting nice for a casual dinner but menu was underwhelming. Waitress encouraged sharing, but not sure how 4 people are supposed to share an appetizer made with 3 bites. The pasta portions could really be an app for one rather than sharable or a main. They were also pushing the crawfish toast - a dish that seems out of place at a restaurant whose self description suggests a local, farm to table ethos (crawfish is neither local to NYC nor in season during September). I did appreciate the hints of Indian spice on a few of the dishes, and the cocktail and wine list were enjoyed all around.
Three different dishes all quite salty.
Rainy day? No problem. The awning saved us.

The ourdoor dining out back was very romantic. Service was great and everyone followed all social distancing etiquette. The food was great. Portions weren't huge but still hit the spot. Very good date spot
Finest place to buy something when in a rush. Their service is efficient, pricing is convenient, fantastic character. Will visit here again

The food was extremely bland, the bathroom was horrendously filthy, and the owner has a very condescending attitude and his breath was horrible. Never eating here again. Not worth the price. If there was a half-a-star option that's what I would rate them.
Lovely outdoor garden and deliciously simple, excellent pasta right in the neighborhood
Delicious, delicately balanced flavors and great service
The patio in the back is awesome.  What great food.  Wonderful and friendly service.

Faun was a chill and welcoming. Don’t let the simple/expected menu options fool you - the menu might seem like you’ve seen it 100 times before, but you have not had it this good! We had the focaccia w/ lemon ricotta and kale salad to start, and shared two pastas (ricotta ravioli and beef Raghu) and a side of broccolini as our main. Everything was exquisite!!! Every bite had mind-blowing flavor and every ingredient had a purpose. Immensely impressed. Great Balfour price. I recommend the skin contact moschofilero from Greece, so flowery and deliciously refreshing.

The vibe is really cute, wait staff was very attentive, and the food was amaaaaaaaaazing. My parents came in from out of town and were blown away by BK dining. We had the scallops ("to die for - I'd order them 20x" - my mom), branzino, caccere (sp?) Pasta, Kale salad and cornbread sundae. It was so delicious
Food and cocktails were amazing!  But the service was extremely slow, although very friendly.

Went here for a brunch with friends and the wait was quite long, but overall I was happy we did it. We got French toast for the table and I ordered the biscuits and gravy with a side of potatoes while my wife got something similar to a personal shakshuka and some focaccia. The Bloody Mary’s were pretty good. I would rather come back for dinner when the weather is nicer so we could sit in the back. French toast I would definitely get again though.

Update. Not sure what we did wrong but the past 2 times we've gone to Faun were not great. Once with clients and another with friends from out of town. Both time servers seemed annoyed at the later seating (8:30 pm) with music being turned off and staff being unprofessional at 10 pm with several tables still seated. We were embarrassed after talking the place up so much. At least I wasn't charged for the steak that was so tough it was inedible. We are really disappointed because we have been coming here since it first opened and we live just steps away.  The food and service is always perfect. With a warm and comfortable atmosphere this is where we bring people to show off in our neighborhood.
Skip all the 'fancy' Italian places on Franklin Ave. Faun is worth the trek! I've been coming here three years and it consistently delivers absolutely amazing food and personable service.
Trendy Italian with  excellent food , craft cocktails, reasonable wine list. Very professional waitstaff. Must visit place on Vanderbilt restaurant row.
Brunch was delightful, service was attentive and space was pretty.
Stellar food and service here.
Wonderful food, great service and great atmosphere. Our favourite place in the area
Awesome
nice place, good wines, good food!!
Amazing food! Really good coffee, and lovely staff/service. We had such good food here and would definitely go back. This place was on the Michelin list 2018 and it shows; awesome place.
Amazing food

We have been to Faun numerous times and have never been disappointed! The wines , starters and pastas are all so delicious.  The space is beautiful and cozy.  The garden is an oasis.  We sat outside a few nights ago and were totally comfortable with the patio heaters.  Highly recommend Faun and can't wait to visit again!

The best al fresco dining in Brooklyn. Pretty and inviting backyard (with heat lamps for fall evenings!) and consistently delicious food- we especially love the pasta offerings which change seasonally. Also, kid friendly :)

Yum! 5 friends and I had the most delicious vegetarian meal there with a perfect wine pairing. The pasta and cheese were phenomenal and very fresh. Can’t wait to go back. Pro tip:  follow their Instagram for drool-worthy photos and recipe suggestions. I roasted some carrots per their recommendation—delicious!
What's great about Faun is the incredible variety of natural wines offered on the menu that pair so well with the house made pasta dishes. Reminds me of a place I used to love called Franny's.

We keep coming back and it’s always a pleasant experience. It is rather small but cozy place and has a lovely courtyard and a nice little bar. The menu has always been great and seems to get even better every time. Excellent and quite particular selection of international wines and local beers.

Want a taste of the sublime on a Sunday?  Eat eggs in purgatory in Faun's back garden on a warm spring morning.  Order spaghetti alla carbonara for the kids -- they will fall silent, diving into their plates, sucking up every strand.  Or sit inside on a frosty winter morning and bask in the light slanting in through the windows and bouncing off the walls.  Drink a perfect latte.  Order more bread.

Recently revisited Faun and it was even better then the last time we were there.  The food has always been amazing but now they have refined the menu. We were a large group so we ended up ordering just about everything on the menu which meant we got to try them all......we would order it all again.  The service and atmosphere is also perfect!
The food is wonderfully inventive but more importantly flat out delicious. The room itself is warm and gorgeous. Hidden gem.
Small menu with every item embodying the platonic ideal of itself!

Gorgeous atmosphere inside and out. Spectacular garden. Nice bar. Mellow vibe, great service. Simple, outstanding menu. Michelin sign in the window for a reason. Priced to perfection for the quality - for us, it’s an occasional but very welcome occasion to go. The food really is amazing. I had the best monkfish of my life, and the pasta was legit killer. Reservations highly recommended. Walk in on the early side (dinner starts at 530) and see what you can get?
It is also a nice place for brunch on the weekends. They have a nice patio in the back, but that does not make it a kid friendly location. Reservations recommended but not required.

We hit Faun for a late, late brunch on a Sunday afternoon. The garden out the back provided a nice table, the service was friendly and efficient and the food choices we had were all a bit different without being too much so. Would like to get back there again.
Delicious food, tasty drinks and great little backyard patio. We’d definitely go back! The shrimp on toast was amazing!
Great food, great drinks, great place. We will back.

What a wonderful restaurant! The ambiance is absolutely spectacular. We sat out on the back patio - Brooklyn’s hidden gem! The food was delectable and the service was top-notch. I look forward to returning soon.

Cozy restaurant with a beautiful outdoor patio and homey feel. Staff is extremely knowledgeable and makes great recommendations. Cocktails were the best I’ve tasted and the Octopus Panzanella was a complete flavor bomb!  Can’t wait to go back for brunch....
Best restaurant I’ve been to

This is my go-to spot to take older relatives who are visiting NYC. Delicious options for brunch or dinner- brunch is a bit more affordable but dinner is still definitely worth it. Excellent location to go explore the park afterwards!
Pleasantly surprised. A bit pricey and wine list is decent
Delicious dinner and drinks in a great atmosphere!
Good American fare well made cocktails. Not the cheapest dinner for 2 but worth the price for a date night. Outdoor seating is a plus.

5 stars all around! Exceptional service paired with exceptional food and drinks. It's an intimate setting, but casual environment so it's perfect for a date or just a night out with friends. You can't go wrong with any of the dishes!
Great service and beautiful back garden! Starters were super tasty but both our pasta dishes could do with some more bold flavours! Personal taste, but would definitely visit again!
Best Italian on the street
Food very good. Excellent staff.
Great place nice environment

The food here is delicious and the staff are hard working and very professional. The seating is a real problem - on rough hewn benches that are too high, we were literally bumped and jostled multiple times by diners coming in to the restaurant and waiting to be seated in the small space between the tables and the bar.  The room was also uncomfortably hot - either inadequate AC or AC not working well. At this price point ($31 entree) I’d expect a much more peaceful and comfortable experience.
Great food and wine selection. The backyard is lovely!
Neighborhood fav

Came here on a date, sat at their little back terrace right before it started to drizzle. The waitress brought out a huge umbrella and let us stay out by ourselves, very romantic. Had their lasagna which was delicious! I've been here for brunch before and also sat outside, it is such a nice little Oasis. Love it!

Wow the food was soooo good, I took my girlfriend to a romantic dinner there and and that was the perfect place to ask her if he wanted to marry me. Romantic place and good food , I’m a Harold’s sous chef and the food was on point mixed greens salad Softshell crab Spaghetti nero Berkshire pork chop Pan-seared atlantic salmon  And the server nice and on point thanks
Really romantic and intimate back garden. Fantastic Italian fare and nice cocktails.
Good food. Cute backyard.
Brunch was amazing. One of The best I’ve had in park slope/prospect area.  Service was even better. Duck confit hash and afagato French toast were standouts.
Don't forget to come here for brunch! Traditional breakfast but with a decidedly Italian twist. Delicious.

Really nice looking place, great service and ambiance. However we found the food lacking. The chicken liver mousse was very flat and missed it's characteristic richness. The accompanying chicken skin and muffins were overfryed and overcooked. The pastas were good as was the caesar salad. I wouldn't rush back here given my favorite restaurant, Olmsted, is across the street.
Our server Kevin was great, would go back just for him.
Is the bast food 🥘

We’ve been fans of Faun since it opened - it’s a lovely local place. I have to say we were blown away by our dinner there last week. Cocktails were delicious (I had the lucky penny) and then we shared the chicken liver mousse, the mezze maniche nero and the poached hake. All delicious. The hake in particular was amazing  (how often do you hear that about hake!) - so beautifully cooked and the beans and kale were perfect with it. The service was perfect. It’s feels like a hidden gem in there. We’re hoping it’s the neighborhoods worst kept secret. An absolute treat.

First time I arrived at this restaurant I wasnt aware that reservations would be necessary but, as soon as I walked in the door and through the curtins I relized how small the venue was.... So BEWARE Reservations are a Must.  About a month later I decided to try again, this time with reservations in place. I even walked in a bit late but thank goodness for the app(RESY) I reserved with because all it took was a text to let the host know.  Let me tell you, the ambiance is romantic and cozy with candle light almost everywhere and dimmed light to really get the night started. And I havent even mentioned their list of alcoholic beverages!! I started with an Antipasti which was Octopus cooked to perfection aka not chewy in the slightest. Then for my Primi I had the Spaghetti which had the best ratio of spice and flavor..... so so good.... Lastly I ended with their Chocolate Boudino which was like a mouse but slightly thicker and super rich in all the best ways.  Only Con I can come up with is the price....but then again I know im not only paying for this well prepared food but also the comfort that comes with eating at such a well put together establishment.  Thanks again to the Staff and Amazing job to the cooks... Ill be Back.

We live in the neighborhood so this will likely become a neighborhood staple for us but this was our second time where the experience was unpleasant.  Our first visit was on a regular Thursday night where they told us they ran out of focaccia. Not a big deal, right? Unless you’re a focaccia fan and checked out the restaurant based on focaccia being on the menu. Other than this, the food and service were great!  We decided to give it another go and spend our NYE at the restaurant. Had late seating, 10pm. We arrived around 1007pm and our table wasn’t yet ready. We were sat 10 minutes to 11pm. The hostess was extremely nice and updated our pricing for the meal, comped our wine, and provided a free glass of champagne. That was all very nice and greatly appreciated.  But...we were disappointed by timing between courses, availability of menu options (some items were no longer available), food temperature, flourless cake was more like cake batter, and of course, there wasn’t ample focaccia to order. So that’s two strikes on focaccia. :-)  We’ll give it a third try soon...
Too much salt in everything
The food is exquisite. Service is friendly, but dishes are slow coming out of the kitchen.
Great cosy yet elevated Italian food. Great atmosphere, great service, great wine. Try it all, it’s really good!
Delicious food, nice outdoor patio. Overall a good restaurant, I highly suggest it.
Great brunch spot near Prospect park. Very attractive cozy interior with beautiful backyard. All the dishes we ordered were tasty. My favs were the arancini, fingerlings and french toast.
The food is always excellent but docking it a star because it is overpriced with small portions.

The food was great and the service even better.  Interesting and good cocktails.  Everything we ordered was tasty. We had the octopus, chicken liver, pork chops, rib and a buckwheat pasta with mushroom.  They were very accomodating for the 2 toddlers we had with us.  I will definitely be back and high recommend this place .
Had a great meal in a comfortable space. The dishes were all flavorful and the menu had just enough variety to keep it interesting.

I really loved everything about this restaurant - starting with the peaceful backyard setting and ending with delicious unique cuisine. Although the menu does not have a lot of options, almost anything you get from the menu is guaranteed to leave your mouth watering for more. The service is impeccable, and the waitresses are happy to help you with the menu choices. Although it says here it’s an Italian restaurant, it’s not a typical one. You have to come and see it for yourself.

The food was good and presented very well but arguably very overpriced (~$20pp for a vegetarian pasta dish). Multiple items we ordered were not available which was disappointing. The atmosphere was nice, the outdoor seating was especially nice and more or less bug free. Overall a positive food experience but not worth the price.
Food was very good, drinks and wine selection was good. Portion sizing on some of the items should be reviewed...great ambiance
extremely overpriced for very small portions. Very slow service. go somewhere else

Excellent food in attractive setting, especially in the spacious garden. The food is very good although one of our party found it too lightly seasoned. The only problem, and it is serious in Prospect Heights, is that they said they could accommodate vegans the only vigan food they could come up with was watermelon. Of course my wife and I were not happy with this, it was embarrassing.
Lovely spot with a great patio. Pasta was lovely. Red snappers are a brunch must.

Faun, as our plan B and last minute brunch choice, definitely exceeded my expectations. A nice tropical and rustic backyard, refreshing watermelon salad, tenderized but also chewy octopus and the flavored potatoes in the Duck Duo Hash -- it's a brilliant decision to come here instead of waiting for an hour long at the other place.
Friendly from the moment we entered. Intimate bar, large patio. The pasta dishes at Sunday  brunch excellent and the duck confit hash was a treat. Would go back in a heartbeat.

Faun was our backup restaurant plan and it was better than I expected. We ordered the 3 course menu and shared the dishes. Their pasta was simple yet delicious. My favorite part of the meal was the fluffy olive oil polenta cake with mascapone and strawberries. Our server was also efficient and knowledgeable about their wines.

Came here a couple of weeks ago and was very happy with this place. We ordered a lot of different dishes they were all very well prepared and flavorful. Somehow squeezed in dessert in the end. We were stuffed but happy. Service was great, the waitress really helped us out with her recommendations.
Perfect wine pairings. Fresh pasta. Never been disappointed.
Very nice garden to enjoy a good Italian dish in the summer. Focaccia and photos were OK, the pasta with chanterelles was excellent. Friendly service.
Great service, great food.  Will go back there for sure.
Great food and atmosphere. Beautiful outside seating.
The outdoor patio, the staff, the food are all excellent.

My first time trying this in downtown Brooklyn! For such a highly rated restaurant, it was very affordable! The service was excellent and the food was on point.The only thing I would say is that the portions or a bit small for how much you’re paying. But the ambience and wine selection made it all worthwhile! Go to Faun if you’re looking for good food, great company ,and great service!

Have been looking forward to trying Faun for sometime and it did not disappoint! The lovely space with its magical green garden backyard was the perfect respite. The food was delicious - unexpected combinations like the marrow arincini topped with roe were fantastic and the fresh pasta dishes which we shared were all wonderful. The trout with artichokes was was a real winner too! Will definitely be back - Full hearts full belly!
Adorable spot with awesome homemade pasta and fantastic service!
I had a great Father's Day here in Faun's peaceful garden. The carrot fritter and trout were both excellent!

Everything was good, but definitely under seasoned. Great staff. Would have liked if our reservation was honored within 15 minutes. We were seated 45 minutes after our reservation after getting there 10 minutes prior.

Got gouged on a group dinner. The $45 prix fixe (for parties of 8 or more) seemed somewhat reasonable, but after every person selected an app and an entree it quickly became clear that we would each be paying $10 or more over the prices visible on the menu?! Ended up being $85 per person with tip (server was fine), moderate amount of drinks and no dessert. Why the markup when our seating arrangement allowed them to sit *more* people and we didn’t linger? Tasty food, but the experience leaves a bitter taste.
Great neighborhood spot. Fine dining in a casual atmosphere. Food was creative and delicious, service was very good. Will definitely return.
Super white restaurant in a formerly diverse neighborhood. Manhattan prizes, not always Manhattan Service. Nice interior. Small plates for the starters and mains.

Went here for brunch, or tried to. Had a reservation and got there on time. The table wasn't ready, they made us wait. They were physically moving tables around. When they finally sat us down, the table was dirty. We at looked at the table in disbelief and the waiter just  said, this is what we have, we're busy. No apologies for being late, no apologies for the dirty table, very rude. We stood up and left.
Amazing place! Love the service, the food and the atmosphere. For brunch, I highly recommend the granola and the focaccia.
Great pasta
Ridiculously long waiting time, waited for appetizers 50 min, 1.5 hours for the main course. food is a bit over cooked. Not the nicest stuff, lady owner is totally ignorant . Won’t come back.

Simple presentations of fine foods served with cheer.  My wife and I since moving to Prospect Heights have put Faun on our shortlist of favorite dinners and brunches and more tellingly our shorter list of restaurants to show off to friends and family visiting from afar.  Why review now? It's Sunday--what else should I be doing?  Today, we stopped in for brunch. Pictured are the Eggs Florentine and the Skirt Steak. Not shown was the Bibb Lettuce and a Latte. Also not pictured is the beautiful, farmhouse inspired interior complete with ship-lap paneling in the back and wooden boxes filled with potted plants that line the walls and windows, and for the warmer seasons a backyard that boasts party-sized tables.  It's worth noting here, that we've never had bad service. Despite the assuming, austere menus the wait staff and management never scoff at a request for a definition or look askance when asked "which do you like more?"  To the food! Speaking to today's meal: The Bibb is massive, refreshing, and deliciously light with a seasonal rotation of fresh toppings. The latte is generous with uniform bubbles and mellow espresso. The Eggs Florentine: perfectly soft with bitter fresh arugula and spinach, generous hollaindaise, and a plump crispy biscuit. My skirt steak was served more rare than I'd liked, but with a peppery fresh-out-of-the-pan sear and too oily chimichuri. The potato wedges, while satisfyingly crunchy had a mushy, dry interior.  From the service, to the atmosphere, to the delicious food, Faun gives you a memorable meal that will have you circling back for the ever-rotating menu.
Inventive seasonal Italian food. Great place to bring your parents when they visit 😜

Small and crowded. Pleasant staff but inconsistent service. Food combos not always well paired. Food varied. excellent pate but with too heavy bread. Some dishes excellent and others quite mediocre. Perhaps we hit an off night. Will try again to see as others have liked very much

Absolutely fantastic homemade pastas. We tried the truffle, the ragu and the capeletti in brodo and all three were fantastic. Will definitely come back. Only suggestion would be to give the option of getting pastas as an main course size. Otherwise, great neighborhood Italian, a real hidden gem.

1) Service was overall good, although it isn't the best of ideas to lean in to cleanup the table so much so that patrons should twist themselves out of the way to allow the overzealous brushing of crumbs on the table cloth. I would suggest recommending the staff to ask customers for their cooperation to allow the cleanup of a table while others are still finishing their dish. If a customer happens to be in the way, once asked they might be amenable to stand or move aside to help expedite the operation. Better yet perhaps, just have staff ask patrons if they'd like to have the table crumbs cleaned away... it might be surprising but some of us might not mind at all especially if there is no need for it and could wait until after the seated party will have left.  2) The napkins are fabric ones and that might be ok as long as they are washed properly. And that also includes to have napkins that won't shed lint all over your face and clothes when used. Our pants and shirts looked like they've had been sprayed with lint. Also it was most unpleasant to use them to dampen one's lips on them. Thankfully I do not have asthma but was enough to bother my breathing too. If that was the consequence of using a cleaning service the owners may want to think about asking the service they use to just dry the naplinsk not bake them until they come undone in the customer's hands. It's very unlikely that the staff setting up the table didn't notice the issue therefore the choice to not address the problem was a conscious one. The best option would have been to use back up napkins and if none were available use paper napkin letting patrons know about the issue and apologizing for it. Returning customers who know would understand that it wasn't because the place is going the cheap route (and it's not like using paper napkins is the same as having to use paper plates to begin with). New customers will appreciate the lengths at which the place went to make the customer as comfortable as possible despite the establishment experiencing some slight issues with the company which is providing them linens cleaning service.  3) The food is between acceptable and pretty good. For those raving about this place I am truly glad for each and every one of them, but I'd suggest to try a few more good restaurants around the world with emphasis to visit both Italy and France (as faun seems to draw mostly from these two specific cuisines) so that they could refine their palate a bit more so that they'd be able to put in a more fair and fitting prospective any restaurant when reviewing it. I am not a Michelin, Zagat or similar food critic despite I have my own mileage. I'm also not a "foodie" getting overly enthusiastic upon discovering contrasting or complementary flavors/textures. It's also not my habit to spend time reviewing an establishment unless I feel it's deserving of the effort. Two-liners and short praises (or complaint) are of little to no importance in my personal opinion. I' care little about someone with unclear culinary and palate refinement experience (and to others I'd fit in the same category) reviewing a given dishes with expressions such as "delicious", "marvelous", "to die for". Without proper context telling why they felt compelled to identify them as such, those are useless. With no description about how scent, smell, flavors, texture, temperature, savory, saltiness, sweetness, etc on played a role in the complex experience which starts the moment a dish is set in front of them (including the presentation of it) such expressions are meaningless. I  do give props whenever they are due and Faun does not deserve a terrible rating (unless your experience went horribly wrong for whatever reason). What is stripping stars off in this unfortunate case are the  issues that would perhaps be considered minor otherwise, if they were not getting in the way of achieving a memorable experience (and dining isn't solely about food). Unfortunately Google decided that's all I'm allowed to write so I'll have to leave it at that.
Sardines were delicious. Pasta was awesome. Cocktails amazing! What a great little restaurant, sad that I only just discovered it recently!
We had the black bass and the pasta special.  The food was incredible. The service was top notch and the atmosphere was just right.   We will definitely return.
Delish!
Best food on Vanderbilt!

Fabulous place to enjoy a lovely dinner. Food was excellent and staff very attentive. Portions are perfect to experience different tastes. Octopus dish was delicious. We will come back in the summer to enjoy the outdoor space. Well done - My (new) favorite place !
Food cooked with imagination and competence.

I have eaten here probably 5 or 6 times. IMHO, they strike a perfect balance of home-iness, haute cuisine and farm-to-table practicality.  Dishes like Honey Lavendar Peking Duck or Carrot Fritters with Steak Tartare evidence a willingness to explore unusual pairings without sacrificing the consuming experience of complete satisfaction.  Brian and his team are absolutely incredible!

Stellar food. All dishes (zucchini fritters, spaccatelli, guinea hen, coffee panna cotta, choco-hazelnut torte) and drinks (red wine) ordered ranged from great to outstanding. Presentation also looked great. The atmosphere was very nice and warm, not too loud. The service was helpful, fast, and attentive. The prices were high and the portion sizes a bit small, but worth the deliciousness. Note that gratuity is included in the prices. We had a reservation, so we were seated immediately.
Great wine selection. Interesting and well executed menu. Friendly, polished service.

My friend had her wedding reception here and it was perfect rustic elegance for an intimate gathering. Cocktails were great and each dish (we were served family style in courses for the reception) was AMAZING. Standouts that I can recall were the octopus, Branzino, salad, and ragu but everything was delicious!

Very nice brunch spot. The outdoor area is very cozy, rustic and alluring in more ways than one. The presentation of the food was very upscale and the prices are very reasonable. This place is great for groups, couples or even single who just want to enjoy a cappuccino and read a news paper.
Cute place with delicious food.

Wow what great and fearless food.  Sardines splayed unapologetically.  Chicken liver with chunky crispy chicken skins.  Pastas that let the simple refined flavors of squid and Calabrian chilis cone through.  Sea bass and corn.  Did I mention the eclectic and wonderful wine list.  A sparkling orange wine? Yes.  Go here.  Often.
Great food, vibe and menu.  Got some breakfast.  Smoked trout and the wife had a classy egg scramble, we were happy.
Very creative and great service which was included.
A bit over priced for the portion sizes and ingredients. Pleasant outdoor seating area.
The Mezze is amazing.  The bar is a perfect place to enjoy a quick meal or just a spritz.

Very nice back garden. The food was hit and miss. We enjoyed the lovely popovers, but not the orange marmalade. It tasted fine, but it's not a popular condiment in the US due to the bitter nature which was exacerbated by the fact that the peels in it were very big. Nice spaghetti carbonara. The duck in the duck hash was very salty. This can be a side effect of duck confit, but I've had it many times where it was not overly salted, so I think there was some heavy handedness. While the scrambled egg and potatoes were good, the steak was flavorful, but incredibly tough on the steak and eggs. I mentioned it to the waiter and he didn't do anything about it. I asked for another steak knife, which he brought, but to me it was the opportunity to do something about. It was like a chew toy. We liked the sausages as well.
Delicious!
Great back patio.
Creative, fresh and crave worthy. Great cocktail and wine program to accompany unique dishes.
Great cocktails and wine, excellent food and dont skip the pasta. Best backyard for dining in bk. Gratuity included.
Delicious food, attentive servers, living wage paid to employees so no tipping

This place is beautiful, the food is delicious, and the service is impeccable. The problem is that their portions are very small and they short pour you on wine by the glass. If you go I suggest buying a bottle of wine and two entrees per person which will end up being quite pricey.
Unique, tasty food! Gratuity included with prices!
Brilliant, from the fluke crudo to the panacotta.

Beautiful interior! Very friendly and welcoming atmosphere. We ate inside, but the garden looks amazing, too. There was a lot of food sharing going on at our table, and every bite was delicious, usually with an unexpected flavor twist. I'll be returning to Faun soon.
Really amazing

Delicious chicken liver mousse. Mezzemaniche with pork ragu was incredible but elusive as a main course. Inviting interior with open kitchen - every passerby slowed to look in. Can't wait to eat in the garden

They had me at Hake.  The most perfectly cooked fresh fish I have ever eaten.  I took my entire family including my 3 and 6 year old picky eaters, all of whom were completely wooed by the end of the meal.  From the fall-off-the-bone boar shank, pork ragu, and homemade pastas, our experience was beyond expectations.  The place, including the magical lighted outdoor patio (heaters situated perfectly for those adventurous enough to brave the cold) was inviting, yet intimate.  Considering the meal prices include service (gratuity), no complaints here - completely reasonable given the quality of food and attentive service.  I would be remiss not to mention that the management, renown and respected Chef, and staff were welcoming, knowledgeable and polite from the moment you stepped inside.  A true hidden gem in Brooklyn worthy of any James Beard or Michelin Star award.
One of the best meals I have ever had. Perfect dinner. Great spot for a date. Lots of room, very cozy, exceptional food and wine. Will return.
Very good restaurant, but probably could've used a bit more salt. A little on the expensive side. Overall had a good experience though.
Amazing octopus and chicken liver appetizers. Salad was pretty plain just some lettuce wouldn't recommend. Pastas were just ok but for main dishes we tried fish and a shank and they were amazing

Was taken by the magical backyard and impeccable service. Faun is a quiet restaurant that sources in seasonal ingredients to make some very very good meals. One that stood out to me was the  sage laminated quadrucci, stracciatella, squash and brown butter second and the wild boar shank. For only being a few months old Faun is really knockout good.

It looks expensive but they add gratuity into the price of the meal so you don't have to worry about tipping. The food fantastic as well as the service. The portion size is healthy without leaving you hungry.

Came here for dinner and loved it. Overall great flavors and cooked well.  LOVED: the octopus starter, swordfish pasta with eggplants, and wagyu. Finished with some coffee.  The hake plate was a little sweet for my taste,though the fish was cooked perfectly.

I ate here last weekend. They had only been open for 1 day, so I was bracing for some chaos.  First of all, the restaurant is adorable-- totally fits the neighborhood vibe and is my kinda place to go to for drinks and some serious eats. (five stars on atmo) The garden was closed due to rain, but looks lovely.  What really stole the show was the food. We ended up ordering the entire menu (no joke) mostly because it all looked good and interesting. The chef comes from some serious pedigree-- former ex. chef of Vinegar Hill House! Hello!!  The stars of the night were the pastas for sure and all the apps I could eat everyday. Entrees were delicious, but I was a bit full by the time they came. ( 5 stars on food)  Service was shockingly good for a new joint and the food came out on time. I like that they take rezzies--so rare in brooklyn-  and not tips. Overall I think this is a great additional to the street!
